etwork not required to verify pre-dispatch enforcement. Rejected Agentic: no dependence on model output quality.","test_description":"Wire real budget config + request construction + dispatch gate with a fake API client. Feed over-budget document and assert module applies configured policy (truncate or reject) and only dispatches compliant payloads.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported token usage for a typical document stays within the configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This depends on provider-reported usage from real HTTP/API behavior; local mocks can trivially echo compliant usage and hide tokenizer/provider accounting mismatches. Rejected Agentic: assertion is about usage metadata budget compliance, not semantic quality of model output. Rejected Integration: in-process fake cannot validate real provider counting.","test_description":"Run a real API request for a representative document, read provider-reported usage fields, and assert total tokens are <= configured budget; fail if provider accounting exceeds local budget assumptions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.79,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior targets retry orchestration across client error handling, backoff timing, and re-invocation logic. This is cross-module wiring but can be reliably reproduced with an in-process fake client returning rate-limit then success. Rejected System: real network timing is not required for minimum failure detection. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: no model-judgment correctness and no multi-step agentic chain.","test_description":"Use fake API client scripted to return rate-limit response first and success second, with controllable clock/sleeper. Assert module waits/backs off, retries, and ultimately returns success instead of surfacing immediate error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
